# SatTrack — Git Workflow

## Branch Flow (MANDATORY)
```
feature/* → development → main
```
Never skip `development`. Never merge feature → main directly. Never tag manually (CI does it).

## Worktree Layout
```
satTrack/
├── satTrack.git/   ← bare repo, NEVER work here
├── development/    ← primary dev worktree
├── main/           ← production (Vercel auto-deploys on push)
└── feature-*/      ← feature worktrees
```

## Commands
```bash
# New feature
cd /Users/goran/Projects/radio/satTrack/satTrack.git
git worktree add ../feature-name -b feature/name

# Merge feature → development
cd /Users/goran/Projects/radio/satTrack/development
git merge feature/name && git push origin development

# Release (development → main) — triggers auto-tag v1.0.X + Vercel deploy
cd /Users/goran/Projects/radio/satTrack/main
git merge development && git push origin main

git worktree list  # from satTrack.git
```

## Commit Messages
`feat:` · `fix:` · `refactor:` · `docs:` · `chore:`

## On Push to Main
- GitHub Actions auto-creates semantic version tag (v1.0.X)
- Vercel auto-deploys (`npm run build`, output: `.output/public`)
